<br>
We have 3 computers, mine runs 98SE but the other two run XP Home Ed. Both the XP comps are from Dell, while mine is home built. Anyway, both of the XP comps have gotten a problem with their paging file (both have the same problem, got it at different times though). When you boot up the computer, it has a message box like so: Your system has no paging file, or the paging file is too small.<br>
<br>
I checked Microsoft's Knowledge Base and found an <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://support.microsoft.com/default.aspx?scid=kb;en-us;315270">article</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> that describes my problem very well. They suggest that the System and Administrators accounts don't have the proper permissions on the drive (one hard drive) -- but when I checked it, they appeared to have full read/write access.<br>
<br>
Oh, and setting the paging file to either System Managed or Custom has no effect.<br>
<br>
