<br>
One correction, make the min/max values identical. Increasing the page file is a good idea, but leaving it variable means that windows has to spend resources managing the size of the page file. By setting the page file to be a static size, you'll make the system more stable.<br>
<br>
DZR, it would probably depend on how much memory you have. XP and/or 2k will manage large amounts of memory much more efficiently than 98 will (98 struggles managing more than 128mb).  (also the HW components/drivers.)<br>
<br>
I've been running xp and eq for over a year now, and have been very happy with the performance (on a GEForce2 video card). <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=381929"> Naladini </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
